A pub landlady is recovering after being bitten by Britain's most venomous spider, leaving a swollen sore on her arm. 

Glenda Roots was bitten on her arm and as she slept in a chair. 

A regular at her pub, The Somerhill, in Tonbridge, Kent posted a picture of the angry red wound on Twitter.

